1. git config --global user.name "Your Name" and git config --global user.email "you@example.com" to set your identity.

2. git init to create a new repository.

3. git status to see the state of your working directory.

4. git add <file> or git add . to stage changes.

5. git commit -m "message" to save a snapshot of your work.

6. git log --oneline to view commit history.

7. git remote add origin <repository-url> to connect to GitHub.

8. git push -u origin main to upload your commits.

9. gir config list - to check what are the changes u made
